---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import FramedPhoto from '../components/FramedPhoto.astro';
import { PERSON, CTA } from '../consts';

// ABOUT — the entity anchor. Person schema is emitted site-wide (BaseLayout);
// this page is its canonical home (rel=author points here).
// Voice: Full LinkedIn Laura. Backstory facts are real (Libbey, corporate
// healthcare, 15+ yrs agency+corporate, MBA, Cincy speaker).
---
<PageLayout
  title={`About ${PERSON.name}`}
  heading="Hi, I'm Laura."
  description="Laura Seelinger is an AI visibility expert and founder of LSX Partners, helping brands and agencies get cited by AI."
>
  <p class="subhead">ai visibility expert · founder, lsx partners</p>

  <FramedPhoto class="img-right" src="/images/laura-kitchen.jpg" alt="Laura Seelinger" shape="oval" reveal />

  <p class="prose">
    I'm the AI marketing nerd who actually looks forward to the monthly reporting.
    I help brands and agencies get <strong>cited by AI</strong> — not just ranked
    on Google. Because when someone asks ChatGPT, Claude, or Perplexity about your
    category, the brand it names (and the source it credits) is the new front page.
    Most companies have no idea what AI is saying about them. That's the gap I live in.
  </p>

  <p class="prose">
    I've spent 15+ years across agency and corporate marketing. Four of them were
    at Libbey, the glassware company in Toledo — I genuinely loved the products and
    the people (I even wrote some of the Amazon copy I now roast in my case studies).
    Most of my family works in healthcare, my husband included, so I spent years
    deep in the world of regulated marketing where the simplest copy change needs
    sign-off from medical, legal, compliance, and brand. That background is exactly
    why I'm useful now: AI visibility isn't just a content problem, it's an
    operations problem, and I've lived both sides.
  </p>

  <p class="prose">
    I don't half-a** things. I test the tools myself — I've swapped my toolkit more
    than once in six months because this space moves that fast — and I run my
    process on real products and real client work before I ever recommend it. My
    clients benefit from learnings months before they'd hit the standard agency
    cycle, because I'm in this every single day.
  </p>

  <p class="prose">
    When I'm not running audits on a Friday afternoon for fun, I'm probably writing
    my newsletter (Cited), speaking at events like Cincy AI Week, hanging out with
    my cats, or asking Claude how to start a fire in a wood stove. I'm 100% myself
    here — em dashes and all.
  </p>

  <p>
    <a class="button" href={CTA.calendly}>Let's talk AI visibility</a>
    <a class="button button--ghost" href={PERSON.sameAs[0]} style="margin-left: var(--space-1)">Find me on LinkedIn</a>
  </p>
</PageLayout>
